The lectures desrcibe the problems related to the study of the NT. On their own the students must read through the entire text of the NT (using a translation into one's mother language) and one standard scholarly introduction to the NT. Lecutures are combined with individual research project thats support the understanding of materials delivered in lectures. Individual research is based on the set of books in library that are used to compare different approaches to a give theme. Students write an arcticle to Wikipedia based on that. Students evaluate the articles of fellow students.
There are also additional learning materials to deepen the knowledge of the field.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will become familiar with the content of the New Testament and with the questions of the NT introduction (results and methods). Students will learn how to do independent critical reseach, how to use Wikipedia format, plan one's time and rehearse cooperation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the completion of the course the student:  1) is familiar with the content of the New Testament (using translation to one's own language) and knows the main answers to the questions of a special introduction to the NT, using one standard scholarly texbook, 2) has a general understanding of the methodological problems related to the study of the NT (the possibilities and limits of different methods) and is able to evaluate critically different approaches to a given theme, 3) has ability to do a research based on different materials  4) and present the research in the format of Wikipedia article (IT-capacity) 5) is able to give feedback to the work done by fellow student 6) is able to plan the time for research and feedback
